component.zwave_me.config.step.user.desc:
Input IP address with port and access token of Z-Way server. To get the token go to the Z-Way user interface Smart Home UI > Menu > Settings > Users > Administrator > API token.

Example of connecting to Z-Way running as an add-on:
URL: {add_on_url}
Token: {local_token}

Example of connecting to Z-Way in the local network:
URL: {local_url}
Token: {local_token}

Example of connecting to Z-Way via remote access find.z-wave.me:
URL: {find_url}
Token: {find_token}

Example of connecting to Z-Way with a static public IP address:
URL: {remote_url}
Token: {local_token}

When connecting via find.z-wave.me you need to use a token with a global scope (log-in to Z-Way via find.z-wave.me for this).
